args:
As the group flees the Imperial Army, it seems
inevitable that the festival will be canceled.
But Cassandra refuses to allow it to happen,
so Curran quickly comes up with a plan to
deal with the troublesome imperials.
For a group of dullards,\nthey certainly are persistent.
Cassandra, do you mind taking the lead\nin guiding our mercantile friend here?
So long as your plan is not to run off\nhalf-cocked and fight them all alone.
If we don't do something, we'll end up\nleading them right to Quinbell.
Perhaps so—but with their numbers,\nI don't fancy your odds fighting alone.\nI will accompany you, dearie.
No. There are fiends in these woods,\nand you need to protect the merchant.
Enough. I will safeguard this man.
You were supposed to return with a\nsingle merchant, yet it appears the\nentire imperial army is at your backs.
Heinwald! ...Heh. And yes, things got\njust a teensy bit out of control.
What brings the two of you out\nto this neck of the woods?
I had a scary feeling about you guys,\nso Heinwald brought me out here.
You were worried about me, Lathna?\nAw, that's sweet.
It's nothing. ...So what do we do now?
Sir, do you mind waiting over there\nfor just a moment?
Er, what are you planning to do?
Beat down some villains, of course.\nNow that we've got backup, we can\nwax the floor with 'em AND save you!
That was a piece of cake!
I'm astounded they would even attempt an\ninvasion with such shabby equipment.
Yeah, but they're still a threat to the town\nif they attack in great enough numbers.
Which, I hesitate to point out, is exactly\nwhat that captain and the rest of his men\nare attempting to do right now.
Yeah, and if they reach it, we're going\nto be hard-pressed to defend it.
We need to get the people out of there—\nthe festival will have to wait.
I know how much you've been looking\nforward to it, my lady, but we have to\nprioritize the town's evacuation.
She's probably about to do something\nVERY stupid, isn't she?
Heinwald, get that merchant back to town,\nwould you? I'm going after Cassandra.
*pant* *pant* The enemy can't be far off...\nIf I have to fight them all by my lonesome,\nthat's exactly what I will do...
Please don't try to stop me, dearie.
Those backcountry troopers will turn tail\nand run at the first sign of my spells.
You know you're being absurd, right?
...Yes, I suppose I do. Perhaps I'm\njust a hopeless old lady in that way.
Oh, I've always been hopeless where\nthat old fool is involved.
I become blinded to reason, unable to see\nexactly how reckless my actions are.
Wait, back up. Who's the ＂old fool＂?
Ah, apologies. That slipped out.\nEr, but don't worry your pretty head\nabout it; it's a tale from long ago.
But in that case, perhaps we can halt the\ninvasion without canceling the festival.
It's come too far to stop it now. Plus,\nI'm still in debt to you, so it's my job\nto make sure this happens.
I'm sorry to be so selfish, dearie...\nbut I am also ever so grateful.
Happy to help. That said, we'll need to\ncome up with a real cracker of a plan...
Which I think I just did!
And what is this plan of yours!
Well, I don't know that it's a plan so much\nas us relying on ＂divine protection.＂
So your ＂plan＂ is to leave all\nin the hands of Ilia?

Hey, if the Goddess wants to throw down
on our side, I'm happy to take it—but I'm
talking more about the kind of divine
protection you get from a festival.
And what sort of protection does a bit\nof festival merrymaking offer?

Well, people do a great deal of praying at
Hinomotoan festivals—and when prayers
happen in such numbers, it's only natural
for a miracle or two to occur.
And then the imperials will be the ones\nwho have to pray their stairs!
Those soldiers from the fort are here!
It's one thing not to evacuate the town,\nbut yer really plannin' to just keep the\nfestival goin' in high gear?
I sure hope ya got a plan.
No—but what I DO have is the power of\nthe festival, which is more than enough.

I totally do not follow any of that.
Er, but the enemy is basically here,
so if we're gonna fight or...whatever,
we better get on it.
We'll stop those laggards in their tracks.\nThey will NOT enter this town.
To arms, everyone! Intercept the enemy!
